formattedAddress: #01-04, National Gal­lery Singa­pore (1 St. Andrew's Road)

tips.text: ask for Yelicia. great service.
Sticky ribs are tasty but rather dry. Get the loaded tacos!
My favourite would have to be the spicy ramen. Good gyoza as well. For some reason, phone data signal is really poor in here, so use their Wifi. Wifi password is 1234567890.
Super cute and fun digital version of the original rotating sushi concept. Tables turn pretty quick so even if the queue looks long, usually not bad
Pancakes with the most awesome maple butter! And thick milkshakes.
Get the membership. Throughly worth it. :)
Kunefe is a must try and u will definitely come back for more!!
Love the beer selection  here! They have more than 30 beers of different flavours for selection. Beer, paired with their skewers 🍢!
Excellent food and you would expect no less when you find out that the former Chef from Taste Paradise is helming the kitchen.
Try the crayfish:)
Oysters from America & France
The carrot cake here sucks. Pls don't eat!!! Hokkien Mee and Oyster omelette sucks. Even the sugar cane tastes diluted
One of our followers recommend the cutlets! Try and let us know if you love it!
Can't choose as there are so many delicious choices. Get a selection box of 9 mini ones only $7

formattedAddress: Suntec City Mall, Sky Garden, North Wing (3 Temasek Boulevard)
location.address: Suntec City Mall, Sky Garden, North Wing

tips.text: Unagi and tempura don 😋 so good washed down with a happy hour beer
The Singapore Slings here are better than at Raffles and the wifi is wicked fast. You can cut your dining budget by visiting during Evening Cocktails. The space is lovely.

formattedAddress: Lobby Level, Grand Park City Hall (10 Coleman St)
location.address: Lobby Level, Grand Park City Hall

tips.text: Nice seafood in lunch
Must bring your family here... The food is high standard,  They have private function room too... Worth the money!!! You will never regret!!!
It's the only churros outfit here that does churros with cream fillings. The cream cheese churros was pretty unique, and the dark chocolate-coated churros hold up better if you're taking them away.
Flash ur fitness first card and get 10%
Service here during weekday lunch is horrible! Probably due I lack of staff.
The fish soup, curry fish head, garoupa fish slice steam boat are the must try dishes!
Try the grilled buns
i still want some more of the  black pepper crab.....
Great food with cheap price ~ free flow of rice. Add on $1.90 ~ from Miso to kaijiru, worth it.
Here for Sunday brunch and left unimpressed with the food. Basilico's brunch is much better. But u do get a good view with nice interiors. Service is also earnest.
